  "doc_id": "21421",
  "text": "Such outbreaks in non-human primates have highlighted the hypothesis of a possible zoonosis in the post-measles eradication era. Until now, due to the fact that SLAM and nectin-4 receptors present high homology in their amino acid sequences between monkeys and humans [CITATION_1] , different studies have shown that CDV could potentially become capable of using human cell receptors [CITATION_2] indicating that CDV infection could be a potential future threat for humans [CITATION_3] , since it appears that so far, zoonotic CDV potential has been controlled by measles vaccination in humans [CITATION_4] .",
